---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteNav from '../../components/SiteNav.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Harness Delta: why the comparison did not run | Prasith Govin"
  description="An evidence note on bounded parity probes, observed process-group cleanup, and the fail-closed blocker that kept an invalid agent comparison at zero model runs."
  ogTitle="Harness Delta: why the comparison did not run"
  ogDescription="A field note on bounded parity probes, fail-closed cleanup evidence, evaluator isolation, and an executable abstention with zero model runs."
  imageAlt="Portrait of Prasith Govin"
>
  <div class="site-shell evidence-shell" id="top">
    <SiteNav />

    <main id="main" class="evidence-note">
      <header class="evidence-hero">
        <div class="evidence-hero__meta">
          <p class="eyebrow"><span aria-hidden="true">07</span>Evidence note / July 2026</p>
          <span class="evidence-status evidence-status--blocked"><i aria-hidden="true"></i>Abstained / no comparison</span>
        </div>
        <h1>Harness Delta</h1>
        <p class="evidence-lead">
          I set out to compare two agent runtimes on six matched tasks. The preflight found that the
          solver and evaluator shared too much of the same machine, and the runtime settings did not match.
          The harness stopped before either model ran. The work since then has made that stop harder to bypass
          and cheaper to trust.
        </p>
        <ul class="evidence-boundaries" aria-label="Claim boundaries">
          <li>No model winner exists</li>
          <li>Zero model runs were executed</li>
          <li>Isolation and parity remain blocked</li>
        </ul>
      </header>

      <section class="evidence-section evidence-section--split" aria-labelledby="problem-title">
        <div>
          <p class="evidence-index">01 / THE FAILURE MODE</p>
          <h2 id="problem-title">A green score would have measured the harness too.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="evidence-prose">
          <p>
            The solver workspaces ran under the same user as the grader. That identity could reach grader
            code, task references, sibling state, and aggregate results. One grader could also execute
            solver-controlled Python inside the evaluator process.
          </p>
          <p>
            Provider, model, reasoning, tool, network, authentication, and fresh-context parity were also
            unproven. Running the matrix would have produced numbers, but those numbers would not support a
            model-quality conclusion.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="evidence-section" aria-labelledby="built-title">
        <p class="evidence-index">02 / WHAT I BUILT</p>
        <h2 id="built-title">The stop condition became executable.</h2>
        <div class="build-slices">
          <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Identity gate</h3>
            <p>The gate probes the current user and available isolation backends. A same-user sandbox cannot qualify as a distinct solver identity.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Data-only protocol gate</h3>
            <p>The evaluator now accepts bounded data rather than solver-controlled code. The same-user identity problem still blocks the run.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Bounded parity gate</h3>
            <p>Capability and authentication probes share a 256 KiB output budget, a strict caller deadline, and a bounded cleanup check.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>04</span>
            <h3>Runner recheck</h3>
            <p>The runner recomputes parity in memory. Saved pass fields and partial evidence replacements cannot bypass the current host result.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="evidence-section" aria-labelledby="probe-title">
        <div class="evidence-section__heading">
          <div>
            <p class="evidence-index">03 / RESOURCE BOUNDARY</p>
            <h2 id="probe-title">A probe cannot spend without limit just to say no.</h2>
          </div>
          <p>The first patch bounded output but merged error text into ordinary output. Review caught it, a new red test reproduced it, and the second patch kept both streams distinct.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="probe-contract">
          <article>
            <span>Ordinary result</span>
            <strong>Two streams</strong>
            <p>Stdout and stderr stay separate. One combined byte counter covers both streams.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>Confirmed stop</span>
            <strong>Exit 124 / Exit 125</strong>
            <p>A 262,145-byte split-stream control or sleeping probe crosses its boundary. The synthetic descendant process group was gone after both overflow and deadline. The successful result records process_group_terminated=true.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>Unconfirmed stop</span>
            <strong>Exit 126</strong>
            <p>Ordinary timeout or overflow is returned only when process_group_terminated is exactly true. Otherwise the reason is <code>probe_termination_unconfirmed</code>, the original cause stays in <code>termination_trigger</code>, and captured output stays empty.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="evidence-section" aria-labelledby="receipts-title">
        <div class="evidence-section__heading">
          <div>
            <p class="evidence-index">04 / RECEIPTS</p>
            <h2 id="receipts-title">What the blocked run proved</h2>
          </div>
          <p>Receipt 020 proves a local fail-closed cleanup control on this host. It does not prove that either runtime is better.</p>
        </div>
        <dl class="receipt-grid">
          <div><dt>Model execution</dt><dd>0</dd><span>model runs executed</span></div>
          <div><dt>Project gate</dt><dd>23 / 23</dd><span>harness tests passed</span></div>
          <div><dt>Output budget</dt><dd>256 KiB</dd><span>combined output cap</span></div>
          <div><dt>Probe timeout</dt><dd>20 s</dd><span>default probe deadline</span></div>
          <div><dt>Cleanup check</dt><dd>2 s</dd><span>termination observation window</span></div>
          <div><dt>Parity and runner</dt><dd>EXIT 2</dd><span>both blocked as expected</span></div>
          <div><dt>Protected surfaces</dt><dd>7</dd><span>reachable by same UID</span></div>
          <div><dt>Public revision</dt><dd>NONE</dd><span>local slice only</span></div>
          <div><dt>Final-slice review</dt><dd>LIMIT</dd><span>independent review unavailable</span></div>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section class="evidence-section evidence-section--split" aria-labelledby="blockers-title">
        <div>
          <p class="evidence-index">05 / BLOCKERS</p>
          <h2 id="blockers-title">The next comparison needs a different topology.</h2>
        </div>
        <ul class="limits-list">
          <li><strong>Distinct solver identity unavailable.</strong> The same UID can still reach all seven protected surfaces on this host.</li>
          <li><strong>Runtime parity remains inconclusive.</strong> Model, provider, reasoning, tools, network, authentication, and fresh context still do not match.</li>
          <li><strong>Cleanup evidence is local.</strong> Synthetic descendants were observed gone after overflow and deadline. A false or unknown observation becomes an exit 126 hard parity blocker.</li>
          <li><strong>Final review remains open.</strong> Independent review is unavailable for this final local slice, so no exact public Harness revision or hosted result is claimed.</li>
          <li><strong>Portability and release remain open.</strong> Cross-platform behavior was not tested, and there is no public Harness revision or hosted replay for this local slice.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="evidence-section evidence-section--split" aria-labelledby="lesson-title">
        <div>
          <p class="evidence-index">06 / FIELD NOTE</p>
          <h2 id="lesson-title">The abstention path needs engineering too.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="evidence-prose">
          <p>
            I used to think parity was mostly a configuration problem. This run exposed a lower layer:
            who can see the answer key, who can execute whose code, and whether those boundaries are enforced
            before the first prompt leaves the machine.
          </p>
          <p>
            The current runner recomputes parity in memory and binds its reports into one generation-bound
            evidence set. The parity gate and runner both return exit 2. Zero model runs are still the result.
          </p>
          <p>
            The improvement is narrow. Hostile or broken probes cannot buffer without limit, and uncertain
            process cleanup cannot look like an ordinary timeout. The cleanup field is a hard parity blocker
            before any model command. Isolation and parity are still blocked.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <aside class="evidence-next" aria-label="Current status and next gate">
        <p class="evidence-index">CURRENT STATUS</p>
        <h2>The local abstention now fails closed when probe cleanup cannot be confirmed. A model comparison stays blocked until distinct identity, exact runtime parity, and independent final review pass.</h2>
        <a class="button button--primary" href="/work/">Browse all evidence notes <span aria-hidden="true">↙</span></a>
      </aside>
    </main>

    <footer>
      <span>© 2026 Prasith Govin</span>
      <span>Evidence before comparison.</span>
      <nav aria-label="Evidence note links"><a href="/">Home</a><a href="#top">Top ↑</a></nav>
    </footer>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .evidence-note { padding: 0 0 120px; }
  .evidence-hero { padding: clamp(100px, 12vw, 170px) 0 110px; }
  .evidence-hero__meta { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 24px; }
  .evidence-status { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 9px; color: var(--green); font: 650 10px/1 var(--mono); letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .evidence-status--blocked { color: var(--amber); }
  .evidence-status i { width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: currentColor; box-shadow: 0 0 0 5px color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 12%, transparent); }
  .evidence-hero h1 { max-width: 1080px; margin: 34px 0 36px; font-size: clamp(70px, 10.2vw, 150px); font-weight: 570; line-height: .86; letter-spacing: -.078em; }
  .evidence-lead { max-width: 920px; margin: 0; color: var(--text-soft); font-size: clamp(20px, 2.2vw, 29px); line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: -.03em; text-wrap: pretty; }
  .evidence-boundaries { margin: 58px 0 0; padding: 18px 0; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px 34px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); list-style: none; }
  .evidence-boundaries li { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 9px; color: var(--muted); font: 600 10px/1.3 var(--mono); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .06em; }
  .evidence-boundaries li::before { content: ''; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--amber); }
  .evidence-section { padding: 110px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .evidence-section--split { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, .86fr) minmax(360px, 1fr); gap: clamp(60px, 10vw, 150px); }
  .evidence-index { margin: 0 0 22px; color: var(--amber); font: 650 10px/1.3 var(--mono); letter-spacing: .09em; }
  .evidence-section h2, .evidence-next h2 { max-width: 920px; margin: 0; font-size: clamp(42px, 5.4vw, 74px); font-weight: 560; line-height: .99; letter-spacing: -.06em; text-wrap: balance; }
  .evidence-prose { display: grid; gap: 24px; }
  .evidence-prose p { margin: 0; color: var(--text-soft); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.72; text-wrap: pretty; }
  .build-slices { margin-top: 62px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); gap: 14px; }
  .build-slices article { min-height: 300px; padding: 26px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 12px; background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface) 94%, transparent); }
  .build-slices article > span { color: var(--amber); font: 650 10px/1 var(--mono); }
  .build-slices h3 { margin: auto 0 16px; font-size: clamp(27px, 3vw, 40px); line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -.045em; }
  .build-slices p { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.65; }
  .probe-contract { margin-top: 62px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-left: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .probe-contract article { min-height: 250px; padding: 26px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; border-right: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .probe-contract span { color: var(--amber); font: 650 9px/1.3 var(--mono); letter-spacing: .07em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .probe-contract strong { margin: auto 0 18px; color: var(--text); font-size: clamp(29px, 3vw, 45px); line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -.05em; }
  .probe-contract p { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .probe-contract code { color: var(--text-soft); font: 600 .82em/1.5 var(--mono); overflow-wrap: anywhere; }
  .evidence-section__heading { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr minmax(320px, 470px); align-items: end; gap: 80px; }
  .evidence-section__heading > p { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.65; }
  .receipt-grid { margin: 62px 0 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-left: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .receipt-grid div { min-height: 230px; padding: 24px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; border-right: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .receipt-grid dt { color: var(--quiet); font: 600 10px/1.4 var(--mono); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .06em; }
  .receipt-grid dd { margin: auto 0 12px; color: var(--text); font-size: clamp(34px, 4vw, 56px); font-weight: 590; letter-spacing: -.055em; }
  .receipt-grid span { color: var(--amber); font: 650 10px/1.3 var(--mono); text-transform: uppercase; }
  .limits-list { margin: 0; padding: 0; display: grid; list-style: none; }
  .limits-list li { padding: 22px 0 22px 32px; position: relative; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--text-soft); font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.55; }
  .limits-list li:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .limits-list li::before { content: '×'; position: absolute; left: 3px; color: var(--amber); font: 650 18px/1 var(--mono); }
  .limits-list strong { color: var(--text); }
  .evidence-next { padding: clamp(52px, 7vw, 86px); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 14px; background: radial-gradient(circle at 90% 10%, color-mix(in srgb, var(--amber) 10%, transparent), transparent 38%), var(--surface); }
  .evidence-next h2 { max-width: 1030px; font-size: clamp(36px, 4.8vw, 64px); }
  .evidence-next .button { margin-top: 42px; }
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .evidence-section--split { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 48px; }
    .evidence-section__heading { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 28px; }
    .receipt-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
    .probe-contract { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .evidence-note { padding-bottom: 76px; }
    .evidence-hero { padding: 82px 0 76px; }
    .evidence-hero__meta { align-items: flex-start; flex-direction: column; }
    .evidence-hero h1 { margin: 26px 0 28px; font-size: clamp(55px, 18vw, 82px); line-height: .91; overflow-wrap: anywhere; }
    .evidence-lead { font-size: 18px; }
    .evidence-boundaries { margin-top: 42px; align-items: flex-start; flex-direction: column; }
    .evidence-section { padding: 76px 0; }
    .build-slices, .probe-contract, .receipt-grid { margin-top: 42px; grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .build-slices article { min-height: 260px; }
    .receipt-grid div { min-height: 190px; }
    .evidence-next { padding: 30px 22px; }
    .evidence-next .button { width: 100%; }
  }
</style>
